        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(qa): crabline channel driver",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThis PR makes QA profile channel drivers executable and separates channel identity from transport mode.\n\n- Adds the merged `crabline` package as a QA Lab dependency pinned to `openclaw/crabline@93b4de9b933b2c32f16f265725a0af3c429997e2`.\n- Runs the `smoke-ci` QA profile through the Crabline runtime via `import(\"crabline\")`, with `channel: telegram` and other requested channel IDs resolved through Crabline instead of an inlined local fallback.\n- Keeps live channel execution on native live transports, where unsupported requested channels fail as missing coverage instead of silently falling back.\n- Makes the `release` live profile fan out to the native Matrix, Telegram, Discord, Slack, and WhatsApp live lane catalogs, then merges their `qa-evidence.json` outputs into one profile evidence artifact.\n- Converts Matrix live QA to emit native QA evidence while preserving its Matrix-specific diagnostic summary.\n\n## Why\n\nTests should be able to ask for a channel shape such as `telegram` while the selected profile decides whether that exchange is handled by Crabline or by a real live transport. `smoke-ci` stays deterministic and credential-free, while live service coverage remains in the live transport lanes and release profile evidence.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check extensions/qa-lab/package.json pnpm-workspace.yaml .github/workflows/qa-live-transports-convex.yml extensions/qa-lab/src/crabline-channel-driver.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/crabline-channel-driver.test.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/crabline-transport.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/crabline-transport.test.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/suite.test.ts`\n- `pnpm exec tsgo --noEmit -p tsconfig.extensions.json`\n- `pnpm vitest run extensions/qa-lab/src/crabline-transport.test.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/crabline-channel-driver.test.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/suite.test.ts test/scripts/package-acceptance-workflow.test.ts`",
